"Gladstone's Name-Game Instructions:"
"Your task in solving this puzzle is to take the  letters from"
"the puzzle alphabet and compile a list of names that will give you"
"the highest score possible."
"No letter may be used more times than is  available  from the"
"puzzle alphabet and no name may be used more than once."
"You will receive points for each name used, as well as points"
"for various letter  combinations  within those names. A Bonus will"
"be added if all letters are used.    Penalty points are subtracted"
"for letters not used."
"Your Solution for this game is scored as follows:"
"For each Name used, you score"
"For each time a Name includes an "
"If you use all the letters, you score a Bonus of"
"For each letter not used, your Penalty is"
"To Create Your Solution:"
"Choose Names from the Source List by clicking with mouse."
"Add Names to the Solution List by clicking on the 'Add' button."
"Remove Names from the Solution List by clicking on the 'Delete' button."
"You may scroll through either list by clicking on the arrows or by"
"moving the sliders.   The scrolling  devices do not operate during Name"
"selection.   They will operate again after the 'Add' or 'Delete' button"
"has been clicked." 
"Your Score and letters remaining are automatically updated follow-"
"ing an addition or deletion."
"Various options are available from the menus: You may load a game,"
"save your  solution to disk, or print your solution to a  printer.  The"
"'Save Source'  and the  sorting and  searching  routines are  available"
"only on the Enhanced Contest Version.   Please see the CONTEST details!"
